	(text "HSE\nFREQUENCY = 24MHZ (2*12MHZ USB RECOMMENDED)\n\nOSCILATORS IN STM32 CAN DRIVE CRISTAL WITH BELLOW GM_CRIT_MAX\nGM (MIN)= 7.5 mA/V   - specified in an2867 table 6.\nGM_CRIT_MAX 1.5 mA/V - specified in an2867  and datasheet table 37\n\nGain margin has to be bigger than 5\nGAIN_margin = gm/gm_crit  \ngm is oscilator transconductance specified in stm32 datasheet\ngm hse =  [mA/V]\ngm lse = [uA/V]\n\ngm_crit = minimal trunsconductance required to maintain a stable oscillation computed from the componet parameters\n\n\nSELECTED\n535-ABM10AIG-24.000MHZ-8-3Z-T3CT-ND\n\nGM_crit = 4*ESR * (2*PI*F)^2 * (C0+CL)^2 \nGM_crit = 4*60 * (2*PI*24MHZ)^2 * (2PF+8PF)^2 \nGM_crit = 0.0005457=0.5mA/V \n\n\ngain_margin = 7.5m / 0.5m = 15 [that is biger then 5]\n\n\nCL = [(CL1*CL2)/(CL1 + CL2)] + CS  {CL1=CL2}\nCL-CS = CL^2 / 2*CL = CLL / 2 \nCLL = 2*(CL-CS)\nCLL = 2*(8PF - 3PF) = 10PF = CL1=CL2"
